         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The inscription mentions Anodikos, son of Kleokrates, and his companions. As emissaries of Assos they transmitted a decree and received an honorary decree in return from an unknown Aeolic city, of which the last three letters occur in the heading of the inscription. The name of the city could be reconstructed as Methymna, Mitylene or a comparable name; for a similar heading (?Aigaevwn), see MFA 84.60=IK 4, 10; cf. IK 4, 11a (?Assivwn) (MFA web entry)</p>
            <p>verification: photo, MFA web entry, Assos; 2023</p></div>
